// src/pages/brands/lg-dryer-repair.astro
// Tier 3 combo page, LG dryer repair (~310 GSC imp/3mo across 10 queries; "lg dryer repair"
// 127 imp pos 35, "lg dryer motor replacement cost" 62 imp pos 9.8 already top-10).
// Built from SERP research 2026-04-30. Tone reference: samsung-dryer-repair.astro combo template
// + lg.astro brand-hub voice consistency.
// Voice discipline: D80/D90/D95 FlowSense vent-blockage codes as LG-unique service depth (no
// other major brand telegraphs vent-restriction percentages this directly), tE thermistor tree,
// DLE/DLEX/DLG model nomenclature, WashTower stacked + TurboSteam variants. NO fabricated names.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/lg-dryer-repair/";

const title = "LG Dryer Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California";
const description = "LG dryer repair across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties. $89 dx. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 (#1346255700410).";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What does the D80 / D90 / D95 code on my LG dryer mean?",
    a: "These are LG's FlowSense vent-blockage codes, and LG is one of very few brands that telegraphs vent restriction this directly to homeowners. D80 means the exhaust vent is 80-90% blocked; the dryer still works but takes substantially longer to dry. D90 means the vent is 90%+ blocked and the dryer begins cycling itself off as a safety measure to prevent overheating. D95 is severe blockage, dryer will not run reliably. Diagnostic and fix is the same: full vent run inspection and cleaning from the dryer back to the exterior wall cap. About 70% of D-series codes resolve at vent cleaning alone (no parts replacement needed). The remaining 30% reveal a secondary issue that the vent restriction was masking, typically a failing FlowSense thermistor, a thermal cut-off fuse on the edge of failure, or a heating element with degraded resistance."
  },
  {
    q: "What does a tE error mean on my LG dryer?",
    a: "tE (or tE1, tE2, tE4 variants) on an LG dryer is a temperature-sensor (thermistor) fault. The control board has lost a valid temperature reading from one of the thermistors that monitor exhaust temperature, drum temperature, or heating element temperature. Three diagnostic outcomes: (1) Open or shorted thermistor, the sensor itself has failed, replacement runs $145-$215. (2) Harness fault, wire from thermistor to control board has chafed or disconnected, repair runs $125-$185. (3) Control board fault, less common, the board is reading the thermistor incorrectly, $345-$525 to replace. Diagnostic order: full reset (kill the breaker for 10 minutes, LG control boards have larger filter capacitors than most competitors). About 10% of tE codes clear at this step. If tE returns, multimeter testing separates thermistor / harness / board in 15-20 minutes on-site."
  },
  {
    q: "What does HE mean on my LG dryer?",
    a: "HE on an LG dryer is a heating circuit error, the control board has detected that the heating element isn't producing heat when commanded. Three suspects: (1) Heating element burned out (most common on electric DLE / DLEX models, year 8-12 typical wear window). Element replacement $285-$425. (2) Thermal fuse blown (vent restriction is the underlying cause 90% of the time, replacing the fuse without clearing the vent fails again within weeks). (3) Gas valve coil failure on DLG gas dryers, $245-$385. (4) Wiring or relay fault on the control board, less common. Diagnostic always starts with vent inspection, LG's FlowSense system means severe vent blockage usually triggers D80/D90/D95 first, but a partial blockage that's outside FlowSense detection range can still drive HE. Multimeter testing separates element / fuse / board in 15-20 minutes."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does it cost to repair an LG dryer?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when work is approved. Common LG dryer repairs at our typical pricing: thermal fuse + vent inspection $145-$245; heating element replacement (electric) $285-$425; gas valve coil replacement (gas DLG) $245-$385; thermistor replacement $145-$215; cycling thermostat replacement $145-$215; door switch / latch $145-$215; drum belt + idler pulley $195-$295 (the squeaking-dryer fix); drum support roller (front + rear bearings) $245-$385; drive motor $385-$580; main control board $345-$525; FlowSense sensor or harness $145-$245. Premium model uplift on LG dryers (TurboSteam DLEX, WashTower vertical stack, SteamFresh variants): 15-20% above the standard band. Most LG dryer repairs land in the $145-$425 range. If your repair quote crosses $500-$600 on a dryer over 8 years old, we'll tell you the repair-vs-replace math honestly."
  },
  {
    q: "When should I replace my LG dryer instead of repairing it?",
    a: "Honest framework. Under year 6: repair almost always, LG dryers should run reliably to year 12-15 with vent maintenance, and a repair under year 6 buys 6+ years of additional service. Year 6-10 with typical thermal fuse + vent + element work, repair is still the right call for most repairs under $400. Year 10-12 with major repair (drive motor, control board, multiple components): repair-vs-replace tilts toward replacement, especially if the dryer is one of the entry-tier DLE2 series. Year 12+: replacement is usually right unless you have a high-spec WashTower or TurboSteam DLEX where the replacement cost is substantial. Cost-of-repair threshold rule of thumb: if the repair quote exceeds 50% of replacement cost AND the unit is over 10 years old, replacement usually wins. We tell you the math on the diagnostic visit before you authorize work."
  },
  {
    q: "Why is my LG dryer squeaking?",
    a: "Two common causes, easy to distinguish. (1) Idler pulley, the spring-loaded pulley that maintains tension on the drum belt. The bearing in the pulley wears, and the squeak is loudest at the start of every cycle and during tumble. Year 5-9 typical wear window. Replacement runs $195-$295 with the drum belt as a paired set (always replace the belt with the pulley, old belt + new pulley fails again within months). (2) Drum support rollers (front and rear bearings the drum rotates on), wear on these makes a deeper rumble or grinding rather than a high squeak, and shows up year 7-11. Replacement $245-$385 typical with both rollers. About 70% of squeaking-dryer calls trace to idler pulley; 25% to drum rollers; 5% to motor bearing. Diagnostic separates them in 10 minutes by listening through a stethoscope or by manually rotating the drum with the belt removed."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you carry LG dryer parts on the truck?",
    a: "Yes, LG dryers are among the brands we stock most heavily because the brand has heavy concentration in our service area. Common items always on the truck: thermal fuses, cycling thermostats, thermistors (FlowSense and standard), heating elements (electric, multiple sizes for DLE / DLEX variants), drum belts, idler pulleys, drum support rollers, door switches, door latches, lint filter assemblies. Less common: drive motors, main control boards, gas valve coils (DLG models), TurboSteam steam generator components, these come from authorized LG distribution, usually 1-3 day lead. WashTower-specific service parts also stocked given the unit's prevalence in newer construction. About 80% of LG dryer repairs we run are completed same-day on the diagnostic visit because the parts are already on the truck."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service LG dryers in Pasadena, East Hollywood, the Inland Empire, and other parts of SoCal?",
    a: "Yes, LG dryers are one of the most-installed dryer brands in our 5-county service area, and we service them from all 8 dispatch territories. The DLE / DLEX electric family is the most common; DLG gas dryers cluster in older homes built before all-electric construction trends. WashTower vertical stacked units are heavily concentrated in newer construction across Pasadena, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, parts of the Inland Empire (Rancho Cucamonga, Temecula), and luxury condo developments throughout the Westside (Santa Monica, West Hollywood, Beverly Hills). East Hollywood, Silver Lake, and the broader Eastside also see strong LG laundry concentrations. The technician on your call comes from the closest branch with the LG dryer parts most likely to be needed already on the truck."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official LG manual or warranty information?",
      a: `For official LG documentation, warranty registration, and authorized service locator, visit <a href="https://www.lg.com/us/support" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">LG official support & manuals</a>. Our technicians work independently of LG's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

