<!-- 07 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">LG dryer jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on LG dryer service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG DLEX7800WE TurboSteam, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> D80 error displayed mid-cycle, taking 90+ minutes to dry a normal load. Owner reported drying times had been climbing for 3-4 months.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Full vent run inspection: substantial lint accumulation throughout the rigid duct run from dryer to exterior wall cap, plus partial blockage at the cap itself (typical of 3+ years without vent cleaning, especially on premium dryers that move more air through the system). FlowSense thermistor tested within spec, heating element ohms-out fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Full vent run cleaning (dryer to exterior cap) plus flexible-duct connector replacement at the dryer back. Verified normal exhaust airflow at the cap (4-finger detection method) and normal drying time on test load.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 75 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG DLE7300WE electric, Sherman Oaks</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> HE error code at startup, dryer wouldn't run any cycle. Owner had reset the dryer and the code returned within 60 seconds.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Vent inspection showed clear airflow at exterior cap. Thermal fuse tested fine. Heating element resistance test: open circuit, element burnout. Year 10 unit, normal element wear-out window. Thermistor and cycling thermostat tested fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Heating element replacement with OEM LG part (in stock on the truck). Full vent run cleaning included as preventive same-trip work to extend new element life. Verified normal heating, full drying cycle, HE cleared.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $345 total. Same-day, 95 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG DLG7301WE gas, Newport Beach</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Loud high-pitched squeak from the dryer at the start of every cycle, getting louder over the past 8 weeks. Cycle complete normally; just the noise was the complaint.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Squeak isolated to the idler pulley, tested by manually rotating the drum with belt removed (silent) vs. with belt installed (squeak reproduced). Drum support rollers tested fine, no rumble. Year 7 unit consistent with idler pulley typical wear window.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Idler pulley + drum belt replacement with OEM LG parts (in stock). Replaced as paired set per standard practice, old belt with new pulley fails again within months. Verified silent operation on full cycle test.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, 65 minutes on-site.</p>
